<A>__{wallace is in the woods, in the grove of trees, looking at marion's hidden grave. the rain falls on his face, like tears. but he has no tears of his own. the cold, the icy rain, the wounds, nothing seems to touch him. with his fingertips he carefully draws her embroidered cloth from beneath his breastplate; hanging in his trembling hands, filthy with the grime and gore of battle, it looks impossibly white, something from a better, purer world.}
